1
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:18,500
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:23,800
<i>[Episode 11]</i>

3
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:36,650
Does she need our help.

4
00:01:36,650 --> 00:01:39,030
Nope. She can do it alone.

5
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:41,730
We'd better not intervene unless the foal is in a poor position for birth.

6
00:01:41,730 --> 00:01:44,230
♫ <i>Standing in the road</i> ♫

7
00:01:44,230 --> 00:01:47,870
♫ <i>Don't know where to go</i> ♫

8
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:52,480
♫ <i>In the air, my memories flow</i> ♫

9
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:55,020
♫ <i>Faces in a row</i> ♫

10
00:01:55,020 --> 00:01:57,920
♫ <i>Take a long way home</i> ♫

11
00:01:58,740 --> 00:02:05,460
♫ <i>But all of this reminds me to believe</i> ♫

12
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:08,940
♫ <i>No one stays or leaves</i> ♫

13
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:16,260
♫ <i>And all of this reminds me to receive</i> ♫

14
00:02:16,260 --> 00:02:19,960
♫ <i>The life we can see</i> ♫

15
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:29,370
Thank you for your help.

16
00:02:29,370 --> 00:02:30,890
I've injected the Tetanus vaccine,

17
00:02:30,890 --> 00:02:32,450
and it has drunk the mare's milk.

18
00:02:32,450 --> 00:02:34,600
Right now, the foal is safe.

19
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:35,530
Thank you very much.

20
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,230
Give me a call if there is an emergency.

21
00:02:37,230 --> 00:02:38,530
Okay.

22
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:52,580
♫ <i>The sun will rise and fall</i> ♫

23
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:01,500
Xie Zhiyao! Come and take a look!

24
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:03,050
The foal is standing up.

25
00:03:03,050 --> 00:03:08,590
♫ <i>But all of this reminds me to believe</i> ♫

26
00:03:08,590 --> 00:03:09,970
Brilliant, right?

27
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:11,990
Foals can stand shortly after birth.

28
00:03:11,990 --> 00:03:13,300
That's the only way it can suckle.

29
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:16,830
In just an hour, it'll be able to roam with the mare.

30
00:03:16,830 --> 00:03:20,820
♫ <i>And all of this reminds me to receive</i> ♫

31
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:24,320
♫ <i>The life we can see</i> ♫

32
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:32,440
Lingdang! See that?

33
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:35,210
The foal has to stand to drink milk.

34
00:03:35,770 --> 00:03:37,960
It's so strong.

35
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:45,030
♫ <i>It's just another day</i> ♫

36
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:46,910
Why am I doing this?

37
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:48,990
Aunty A'Gui called Uncle Zeqing home for dinner.

38
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:51,260
He has to keep watch at night.

39
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,700
I'm asking, why am I doing this?

40
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:56,180
Shouldn't you thank me?

41
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:58,810
I gave you the chance to witness the birth of a life.

42
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:03,420
Dinnertime!

43
00:04:06,590 --> 00:04:09,000
I saw you cry this afternoon.

44
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,890
I was a little touched.

45
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:14,320
It's a rare scene for city folks like you.

46
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:18,040
For us, our family always reared livestock.

47
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:21,490
Chopping firewood in the mountains, picking mushrooms,

48
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:23,820
and farming the land are part of our daily lives.

49
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:25,050
I'm not a city girl.

50
00:04:25,050 --> 00:04:26,760
I was born in a small town.

51
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,040
My grandma lived in the countryside.

52
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:30,980
When I was a child, I'd visit her during vacations.

53
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:33,470
I used to catch fish in the brooks!

54
00:04:33,470 --> 00:04:35,840
I even hatched eggs myself!

55
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:38,400
How did you do that?

56
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,510
I put the eggs in my pockets

57
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:43,640
and kept them in my hands except for mealtimes.

58
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,620
My grandma said people cannot hatch eggs, but my sister said we could.

59
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:52,690
My sister said most people can't do so because they lack persistence.

60
00:04:52,690 --> 00:04:54,620
Whose opinion did you believe?

61
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:58,290
I wanted to prove my persistence.

62
00:04:58,290 --> 00:04:59,320
What happened?

63
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,330
The chick was hatched.

64
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:05,110
- Really?
- It's true!

65
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:07,820
You can't lie to me because I lack education.

66
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,500
It's true.

67
00:05:14,870 --> 00:05:16,460
<i>Sister.</i>

68
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:18,330
<i>Can you hold them for ten minutes for me?</i>

69
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:19,750
<i>I'll take a quick shower.</i>

70
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,500
<i>You always ask me to hold them for you.</i>

71
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,900
<i>When the chicks are hatched, they'll be mine to eat when they're bigger.</i>

72
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,740
<i>You can't eat them!</i>

73
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:26,800
<i>Fine, off you go.</i>

74
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,860
<i>You only have ten minutes.</i>

75
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:30,490
<i>Hurry up.</i>

76
00:05:57,580 --> 00:06:01,020
<i>I swapped the eggs with boiled ones.</i>

77
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:07,520
<i>What about the raw eggs?</i>

78
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:09,530
<i>I put them in the henhouse.</i>

79
00:06:09,530 --> 00:06:11,570
<i>I was afraid she'd break them.</i>

80
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,840
<i>Have some more.</i>

81
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:23,400
<i>A hen only takes care of the chicks hatched by itself.</i>

82
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:28,060
<i>So, before the chick is hatched, we must put the eggs in the henhouse.</i>

83
00:06:31,310 --> 00:06:33,970
<i>Turn around. Don't look.</i>

84
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,440
<i>No peeping!</i>

85
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,070
<i>Hongmi, keep an eye on Dou Dou.</i>

86
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:43,660
<i>Make sure she doesn't peep.</i>

87
00:06:43,660 --> 00:06:45,480
<i>Go over there.</i>

88
00:06:55,070 --> 00:06:56,220
<i>All done.</i>

89
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:59,090
<i>We just have to wait for the chicks to hatch.</i>

90
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:04,590
<i>Sister! Look!</i>

91
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:08,010
<i>Amazing! You're our Hatching General!</i>

92
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,120
When did you find out?

93
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,880
In junior high school.

94
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:15,620
My sister was taking the college entrance examinations.

95
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:18,760
My dad said she could go to Fudan University.

96
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:20,860
Then, she burst out laughing,

97
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:24,450
saying that I should apply for the University of Hatching Eggs.
<i>("Fudan" sounds like "hatching eggs")</i>

98
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:27,160
Your sister is pretty good at keeping secrets.

99
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:31,090
My sister had a hand in tricking me

100
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:33,650
every step of the way as I grew up.

101
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:17,800
- Is it too tight?
- Nope.

102
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,090
Sister. I washed the dishes. I'm heading to work.

103
00:08:20,090 --> 00:08:22,470
Uncle, take me with you.

104
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:25,340
I'm busy this weekend. You can't tag along. Why not play with Guobao and the others?

105
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:28,340
Tuotuo invited Guobao, Huzi, and me

106
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:30,100
to the cafe for cakes.

107
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:32,670
Wait for her. I'm almost done with braiding her hair.

108
00:08:32,670 --> 00:08:34,470
What a hassle.

109
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,040
It won't take long.

110
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:43,120
Sister, it's Mr. Bow Legs.

111
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:46,230
Don't you call my dad names. Apologize.

112
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:48,100
I'm sorry. Pick it up.

113
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:50,140
I need to use the bathroom.

114
00:08:53,020 --> 00:08:54,510
Dad!

115
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:55,680
<i>Do you miss me?</i>

116
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,160
I do! Are you coming to visit me?

117
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,470
<i>Where's your mom?</i>

118
00:08:59,470 --> 00:09:01,150
She's beside me.

119
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:03,120
She's braiding my hair prettily.

120
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,320
I have a date today.

121
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:08,370
That's not a date. Don't be silly.

122
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,610
All done.

123
00:09:10,610 --> 00:09:12,760
Give me the phone. You can check if your uncle is done.

124
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,140
- Dad, I'm leaving.
<i>- Okay.</i>

125
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:16,620
Off you go.

126
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:19,910
What's up?

127
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:21,610
<i>I just called Mom.</i>

128
00:09:21,610 --> 00:09:23,840
<i>I'm thinking of visiting Xiao Hu Lu next month.</i>

129
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,470
<i>She asked me to talk to you.</i>

130
00:09:25,470 --> 00:09:27,270
Sure, you can come.

131
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,590
<i>I'll go over then.</i>

132
00:09:29,590 --> 00:09:31,990
Just call me next time.

133
00:09:31,990 --> 00:09:34,870
Stop calling my mom and Xia Xia.

134
00:09:34,870 --> 00:09:37,650
<i>Well, I... I...</i>

135
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:38,890
Are you seeing someone now?

136
00:09:38,890 --> 00:09:40,310
<i>I'm not!</i>

137
00:09:40,310 --> 00:09:42,140
<i>Why would I do that?</i>

138
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:46,390
I thought you were dating someone and didn't want to piss her off.

139
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:48,150
<i>I'm afraid you'd be annoyed by me.</i>

140
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:49,220
Don't worry.

141
00:09:49,220 --> 00:09:52,250
For Xiao Hu Lu's sake, I won't be annoyed at you.

142
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:55,200
By the way, Luo Quan, we divorced three years ago.

143
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:58,150
You can get a girlfriend or even get married if you want.

144
00:09:58,150 --> 00:10:00,530
I've talked to Xiao Hu Lu about it.

145
00:10:00,530 --> 00:10:02,800
Don't worry about that.

146
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,690
<i>Do you have a boyfriend now?</i>

147
00:10:04,690 --> 00:10:06,210
Mind your own business.

148
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:08,340
That's all. I'm heading to work.

149
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:10,260
Remember to send my regards to your parents.

150
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:12,760
<i>Take care of yourself. Don't work too hard.</i>

151
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,310
You too. Got to go.

152
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:30,350
The orange juice. Don't work too hard.

153
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:34,200
I'll give you a fruit platter if you're still hungry after the desserts.

154
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:37,880
Children shouldn't eat too many sweets. Got it?

155
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,650
What's wrong? Why are you so gloomy?

156
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:48,900
Tuotuo is leaving.

157
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:51,750
- Where to?
- Somewhere very far away.

158
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:53,570
My dad will be a driver there.

159
00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:56,140
My mom will sell flowers.

160
00:10:58,650 --> 00:10:59,980
It's okay.

161
00:10:59,980 --> 00:11:02,080
You can still call each other.

162
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,520
Tuotuo can come here during school vacations.

163
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:06,080
You can still hang out together.

164
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:08,720
But, right now, we have fun together every day.

165
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,940
Why can't you stay at home?

166
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:13,150
Your grandparents are staying here.

167
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:16,670
Yeah, why do you have to go?

168
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:31,140
It's not that far.

169
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:32,810
My dad, grandpa, grandma,

170
00:11:32,810 --> 00:11:34,930
Uncle A'Yao's dad, and aunt,

171
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:37,670
and Uncle A'Yuan all live there.

172
00:11:37,670 --> 00:11:39,380
Sister Na Na is right.

173
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:41,030
We can call each other.

174
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:43,350
Will we still be best friends?

175
00:11:43,350 --> 00:11:44,430
Of course.

176
00:11:44,430 --> 00:11:46,670
Promise us that you won't have other best friends.

177
00:11:46,670 --> 00:11:50,520
I promise. The three of you will be my only best friends.

178
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:51,850
Really?

179
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:55,960
Will I still be your best friend?

180
00:12:19,900 --> 00:12:22,390
It's no big deal. Stop crying.

181
00:12:22,390 --> 00:12:24,530
Let's have desserts.

182
00:12:42,910 --> 00:12:45,570
Did someone beat up Guobao?

183
00:12:46,790 --> 00:12:49,420
There, there. Calm down.

184
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:51,430
There, there.

185
00:12:51,430 --> 00:12:53,020
Here I am!

186
00:12:53,770 --> 00:12:55,420
A double-shot Iced Americano, right?

187
00:12:55,420 --> 00:12:56,960
In a minute.

188
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:02,190
Who's that?

189
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:04,540
Ponytail? What happened?

190
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:06,350
He's crying so badly.

191
00:13:06,350 --> 00:13:09,360
Kids are so unpredictable, just like the weather in June.

192
00:13:10,590 --> 00:13:13,520
By the way, when I left the courtyard,

193
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:16,300
I saw Xu Hongdou writing an employee manual.

194
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:18,230
You guys sure have your tricks.

195
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:20,640
She's taking a holiday here, but look what she's doing.

196
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,920
You coaxed her into working for you free of charge.

197
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,380
That's beyond me.

198
00:13:24,380 --> 00:13:27,100
Chairman Xie persuaded her.

199
00:13:29,690 --> 00:13:32,330
No surprises there. Never trust a man's word.

200
00:13:32,330 --> 00:13:33,930
Everything he utters is a lie.

201
00:13:33,930 --> 00:13:35,540
Aren't you a man, too?

202
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:39,670
Are you jealous because Hongodu prefers Chairman Xie over you?

203
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:40,830
Bingo.

204
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:42,620
None of you hang out with me.

205
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:44,400
I'm angry.

206
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,430
Jiahui.

207
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:22,510
Having your meal? Good cat.

208
00:14:22,510 --> 00:14:24,330
Don't run away.

209
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,940
Holy hells!

210
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:43,700
Have you reached the stage of meditating with your eyes open?

211
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:47,730
Mr. Ma, you're reaching enlightenment soon.

212
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,960
Jiahui.

213
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:55,040
Have some water.

214
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:59,980
Aunty A'Gui, want to join me for tea?

215
00:15:00,620 --> 00:15:03,240
Sure, get me some.

216
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:09,380
Hongdou, let's take a break.

217
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:11,570
Mr. Ma is making tea. Come over and have some.

218
00:15:11,570 --> 00:15:13,320
Sure.

219
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:27,310
Hongdou, I heard from the villagers that you're tending the shop for A'Yao.

220
00:15:27,310 --> 00:15:29,020
Are you planning to stay here?

221
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:30,100
No, no.

222
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:32,730
I'm just a volunteer. I work for free.

223
00:15:32,730 --> 00:15:36,440
- I'm helping him out.
- Helping him out?

224
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,780
Good for you.

225
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:40,850
We have to keep ourselves busy.

226
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:43,710
Laziness is a disease.

227
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,800
She's talking about me. Have some tea.

228
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,430
Thank you.

229
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:00,170
It smells great.

230
00:16:00,170 --> 00:16:01,940
This tastes pretty nice.

231
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:05,510
But... it just tastes like tea.

232
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:13,440
Aunty A'Gui, your words are overflowing with Zen.

233
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,020
It's a cup of tea.

234
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:17,670
That's all it should be.

235
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:21,030
I only finished elementary school, so I'm not good with words.

236
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:22,940
Don't mock me.

237
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:25,840
Your words are full of wisdom.

238
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,910
It's so hard to understand what he says.

239
00:16:29,910 --> 00:16:32,690
I know. It's strenuous to communicate with me.

240
00:16:32,690 --> 00:16:35,640
It's understandable that you're not fond of me.

241
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:39,640
Hongdou, isn't he hilarious?

242
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,380
We all eat grains.

243
00:16:42,380 --> 00:16:45,240
Burping, farting, and grinding our teeth are all parts of our lives.

244
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:48,020
We should spend our day working.

245
00:16:48,020 --> 00:16:50,410
We can never rest.

246
00:16:50,410 --> 00:16:54,500
We must take good care of the elderly and children.

247
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:57,020
Living is painstaking.

248
00:16:57,020 --> 00:17:01,110
Only if you're dead and six feet under, then you can finally rest.

249
00:17:01,110 --> 00:17:02,730
Aren't I right?

250
00:17:05,540 --> 00:17:10,240
In our village, people your age have children in junior high school.

251
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:12,940
Why would someone squander his time sitting there?

252
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:15,980
You can't support your family by sitting there.

253
00:17:18,030 --> 00:17:20,440
That's one way of thinking.

254
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:24,240
However, as long as someone can live on his own

255
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:26,800
without harming others,

256
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:30,120
he has the right to freely choose the life he wants to live.

257
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:31,380
Don't you agree?

258
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:33,910
When it comes to freedom,

259
00:17:33,910 --> 00:17:39,780
only an orphan can be truly free to choose the life they want.

260
00:17:40,590 --> 00:17:42,310
If you have family,

261
00:17:42,310 --> 00:17:45,150
you have to spare a thought for them.

262
00:17:45,150 --> 00:17:48,450
If you're lazing away, they'll have to work hard.

263
00:17:48,450 --> 00:17:50,120
If you sit there,

264
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:53,520
they'll have to strive harder for a living.

265
00:17:55,550 --> 00:17:58,200
Visitors like you guys always say

266
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,470
an unrestrained life is the best as long as you obey the law.

267
00:18:00,470 --> 00:18:03,110
You can do whatever you want.

268
00:18:03,820 --> 00:18:05,900
Here's a question for you.

269
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:10,400
What if you're starving out there?

270
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,940
Who will take care of you?

271
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:16,810
Your parents will get old and fall sick.

272
00:18:16,810 --> 00:18:21,440
You'll need money for your own emergencies,

273
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:23,840
but you don't have any.

274
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:25,780
What are you going to do then?

275
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:29,150
It's too late to start scrimping for money.

276
00:18:33,820 --> 00:18:35,480
Aunty A'Gui,

277
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:40,350
a single chat with you is more insightful than ten years of studying.

278
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:43,000
I'm just blabbing.

279
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:46,000
Don't take my words too seriously.

280
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,880
You've made your point clearly.

281
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:53,160
I can't let such wisdom go to waste. That'll be just like letting cows eat peonies.

282
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:57,100
Why would a cow eat peonies?

283
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,270
Why would a cow...

284
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:02,590
The reason doesn't matter.

285
00:19:02,590 --> 00:19:04,960
The food it's eating doesn't matter either.

286
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,560
Here's what I mean.

287
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:11,680
I'm sitting here to resist my diligence.

288
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:14,300
Pitting stasis against all motion.

289
00:19:18,270 --> 00:19:20,690
Do you understand a word he's saying?

290
00:19:25,550 --> 00:19:28,800
I see your mouth moving, but the sentences

291
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,860
don't quite make sense.

292
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:34,010
Simply put,

293
00:19:34,010 --> 00:19:37,000
the Pareto principle applies to everything.

294
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:41,210
Oftentimes, even if you try hard and devote yourself to your task,

295
00:19:41,210 --> 00:19:44,970
all your efforts may just be in vain.

296
00:19:44,970 --> 00:19:48,670
Since your efforts will go to waste, why bother at all?

297
00:19:48,670 --> 00:19:56,060
Well... Isn't it better to cope with change and motion with stasis?

298
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:59,260
That's true wisdom.

299
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:05,890
I get it now.

300
00:20:05,890 --> 00:20:08,920
However, you're preaching to the wrong person.

301
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:12,120
I can't help you.

302
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:16,810
In our lives,

303
00:20:16,810 --> 00:20:18,590
we're born with nothing on.

304
00:20:18,590 --> 00:20:21,500
When we die, we take nothing with us.

305
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:24,100
Life is arduous,

306
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:28,870
but you can't end your life because you're going to die.

307
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,930
Only the air you breathe in is free.

308
00:20:31,930 --> 00:20:34,810
Everything else comes at a price.

309
00:20:34,810 --> 00:20:37,010
Can you stay still forever?

310
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:41,780
If you can't, go and get a job!

311
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:44,770
You don't have to be the boss.

312
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:52,460
Besides, let's assume you're a boss,

313
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:57,540
a billionaire rolling in the cash.

314
00:20:57,540 --> 00:20:59,320
Your money...

315
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:02,210
can fill the entire yard here.

316
00:21:02,210 --> 00:21:04,770
A bottomless pit of wealth.

317
00:21:06,170 --> 00:21:08,700
Here's my question for you.

318
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:12,380
What if you die?

319
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:16,410
Can you take all these with you?

320
00:21:18,450 --> 00:21:21,460
They're meaningless to a dead person.

321
00:21:21,460 --> 00:21:23,860
How about paper effigies,

322
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:29,640
cars, houses, villas, paper dolls, and banknotes of hundreds of billions?

323
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:31,880
You name it.

324
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:34,620
It won't cost a fortune for others to buy all these and burn them for you.

325
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:38,480
to buy all these and burn them for you.

326
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:40,400
Right?

327
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:54,480
I hate talking about such things.

328
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:56,940
It's just small talk, so don't take my words seriously.

329
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:58,710
I'm done with chatting.

330
00:21:58,710 --> 00:22:01,540
I need to get back to work.

331
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:04,410
Wait. Don't leave.

332
00:22:04,410 --> 00:22:07,390
Blackie, don't step on my flowers!

333
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:10,970
True wisdom.

334
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:16,240
Worthy of the classics.

335
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:18,750
I'm enlightened.

336
00:22:25,820 --> 00:22:28,230
Let's have some tea.

