<i>[Chapter 126]</i>

339
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:28,670
<i>[Chapter 126]</i>

340
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:27,980
Damai, you scared me.

341
00:25:27,980 --> 00:25:30,020
Mr. Ma.

342
00:25:30,020 --> 00:25:32,090
Do you want some food?

343
00:25:32,090 --> 00:25:33,460
What are you making?

344
00:25:33,460 --> 00:25:34,710
Rice vermicelli.

345
00:25:34,710 --> 00:25:37,340
Tottering rice vermicelli.

346
00:25:37,340 --> 00:25:39,340
Rice vermicelli with a toddler?

347
00:25:44,150 --> 00:25:46,050
Is a calf in it?

348
00:25:46,050 --> 00:25:48,120
That's not it.

349
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:50,750
Man makes mistakes, just like a horse may totter.

350
00:25:50,750 --> 00:25:52,400
My last name means horse.

351
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:55,170
So, I'm making tottering rice vermicelli.

352
00:25:57,550 --> 00:25:58,870
Want some of it?

353
00:25:58,870 --> 00:26:01,380
Yes, please. Thank you.

354
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:12,010
Are you running out of inspiration for writing?

355
00:26:14,030 --> 00:26:16,870
Why are you feeling stressed out?

356
00:26:21,540 --> 00:26:26,260
Reader comments, my income, and my inability to write.

357
00:26:26,260 --> 00:26:28,750
Why can't you write?

358
00:26:28,750 --> 00:26:31,400
Reader comments and my income.

359
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:33,390
It's a vicious cycle.

360
00:26:34,310 --> 00:26:35,650
Does your family support your job?

361
00:26:35,650 --> 00:26:38,880
My mom does, but my dad doesn't.

362
00:26:40,780 --> 00:26:43,870
Does he think it's an unstable job?

363
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:46,400
It's more than that.

364
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:48,280
He thinks it's humiliating.

365
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:51,350
Writing is humiliating?

366
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:53,550
Why?

367
00:26:53,550 --> 00:26:56,310
When I started with web novels,

368
00:26:56,310 --> 00:26:59,610
I wrote some fan fiction with explicit scenes.

369
00:26:59,610 --> 00:27:01,540
After that, I became a full-time web novelist.

370
00:27:01,540 --> 00:27:03,510
My 15-year-old cousin

371
00:27:03,510 --> 00:27:06,250
found those fan fiction when searching for my work online.

372
00:27:06,250 --> 00:27:09,670
She sent them to her classmates, and the entire class knew about them.

373
00:27:09,670 --> 00:27:12,040
To make things worse, she bragged that her cousin wrote them.

374
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:14,340
Eventually, their form teacher found out.

375
00:27:14,340 --> 00:27:16,440
After the form teacher grasped the situation,

376
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:18,510
she spoke to her colleague, Mr. Zhou.

377
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:20,910
That colleague is my dad.

378
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:24,450
He shot to fame in school thanks to me.

379
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:29,600
But I quit writing fan fiction when I became a full-time web novelist.

380
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:32,730
I started to write original fiction about mystery and romance.

381
00:27:32,730 --> 00:27:34,950
But my dad is still against my job.

382
00:27:34,950 --> 00:27:38,370
I graduated from a normal university, so he wants me to be an elementary school teacher.

383
00:27:38,370 --> 00:27:39,720
He thinks that'll help me find a husband.

384
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:42,390
I even get summer and winter vacation to spend with my family.

385
00:27:43,350 --> 00:27:45,930
A parent's love for their children

386
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:49,260
leads them to make long-term plans for you.

387
00:27:51,970 --> 00:27:55,320
Damai, here's my advice.

388
00:27:55,820 --> 00:27:59,210
If we keep looking at the ground

389
00:27:59,210 --> 00:28:02,090
and following our parents' footsteps while marching forward,

390
00:28:02,090 --> 00:28:04,700
we can never find a new path.

391
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:08,930
You have to pave your own path.

392
00:28:11,250 --> 00:28:14,910
However, it will be a path

393
00:28:14,910 --> 00:28:19,610
full of thorns and obstacles.

394
00:28:19,610 --> 00:28:23,900
What's worse, there might be tigers and wolves lurking in the darkness.

395
00:28:23,900 --> 00:28:25,910
But don't worry.

396
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,900
It won't always be like that.

397
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:32,980
Every dog has its day.

398
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:37,470
One day, you'll see cows and sheep grazing on fields of blooming flowers.

399
00:28:37,470 --> 00:28:42,390
You'll race on horseback and bellow with pride.

400
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:46,890
Mr. Ma, will perseverance lead me to these flowers?

401
00:28:46,890 --> 00:28:49,730
You'll see grass and woods pass.

402
00:28:49,730 --> 00:28:52,000
Will I ever reach the flowers?

403
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:55,520
All done.

404
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:58,010
Wash your hands. Get the bowls.

405
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:35,580
Delicious.

406
00:29:37,490 --> 00:29:39,750
That's what I really wanted to hear.

407
00:29:40,310 --> 00:29:44,540
Mr. Ma, you haven't answered my question. Will I ever reach the flowers?

408
00:29:44,540 --> 00:29:46,590
Don't talk while eating.

409
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:37,280
Now it's time to talk about your flowery road.

410
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:39,170
Flowery road?

411
00:30:40,650 --> 00:30:42,510
Flowery road!

412
00:30:43,450 --> 00:30:48,130
Certain topics should be left for a full stomach,

413
00:30:48,130 --> 00:30:50,150
especially when it's late at night.

414
00:30:50,150 --> 00:30:52,490
When silence embraces us,

415
00:30:53,140 --> 00:30:55,820
when most creatures go to sleep,

416
00:30:55,820 --> 00:30:58,840
when you let your guard down,

417
00:30:58,840 --> 00:31:01,350
replenishing your energy...

418
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:03,970
feels wonderful.

419
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:13,000
I'll be frank with you.

420
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:20,380
You can't always find a flowery path.

421
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,620
Take my...

422
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:28,490
my friend as an example.

423
00:31:29,140 --> 00:31:31,320
He was filled with arrogance,

424
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:36,680
thinking he could achieve anything he desired.

425
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:41,650
When the internet started to thrive, he undertook all kinds of jobs.

426
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:46,620
This lad was pretty lucky and opportunistic.

427
00:31:46,620 --> 00:31:51,440
He always pulled out right before the recessions.

428
00:31:52,480 --> 00:31:55,400
His wealth kept snowballing.

429
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:58,200
Arrogant as he was, he rented several floors

430
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:03,870
at the most luxurious science park in Beijing.

431
00:32:03,870 --> 00:32:05,590
It was over 10,000 square meters.

432
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:07,350
He hired hundreds of employees.

433
00:32:07,350 --> 00:32:09,250
He wanted to make it big this time.

434
00:32:09,250 --> 00:32:12,350
So, he invested all his money to be the best.

435
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,150
He failed.

436
00:32:20,590 --> 00:32:24,240
He lost all the money he earned over the past few years.

437
00:32:25,030 --> 00:32:29,200
He sold his villa and his luxury car for money.

438
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:32,570
Thankfully, he had a conscience.

439
00:32:32,570 --> 00:32:35,520
He paid all the wages

440
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:40,680
and settled all the balance payments.

441
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:45,280
When he did the accounts,

442
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:48,540
his years of effort had gone down the drain.

443
00:32:48,540 --> 00:32:51,070
He didn't make a single penny nor was he in debt.

444
00:32:53,590 --> 00:32:56,200
What's he doing now?

445
00:32:56,650 --> 00:32:58,970
Nothing at all.

446
00:33:00,350 --> 00:33:04,100
In the past, he had his sights on the world.

447
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:08,250
Right now, he's reflecting on himself.

448
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:11,720
He isolates himself from the bustling world...

449
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,120
and uses the bare energy left in him

450
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:20,070
to suppress his restless desire to restart his career.

451
00:33:20,790 --> 00:33:22,310
Does he still want to be an entrepreneur?

452
00:33:22,310 --> 00:33:24,310
Isn't that funny?

453
00:33:24,310 --> 00:33:29,020
Someone else would've quit by now.

454
00:33:30,030 --> 00:33:32,140
But him?

455
00:33:32,140 --> 00:33:38,010
The fire... in his heart...

456
00:33:39,070 --> 00:33:41,960
is still blazing.

457
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:44,700
He's reluctant to work for others.

458
00:33:45,450 --> 00:33:49,540
All he does now is sit still.

459
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:58,640
I reckon he's just not interested in anything else.

460
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:04,650
It's the same for me.

461
00:34:04,650 --> 00:34:08,760
I'm only interested in writing,

462
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:14,000
but we must face reality.

463
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:19,090
Face reality?

464
00:34:20,190 --> 00:34:22,660
What reality?

465
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:26,360
I'm a 28-year-old writer with zero popularity

466
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:28,930
and a pathetic number of subscribers.

467
00:34:28,930 --> 00:34:32,810
I'm being heavily plagiarized while receiving mean comments from readers.

468
00:34:32,810 --> 00:34:34,780
My parents doubt me,

469
00:34:34,780 --> 00:34:38,670
and my future is bleak.

470
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:44,750
That's miserable.

471
00:34:46,630 --> 00:34:52,320
It reminds me of the comments from my friend's parents on his career.

472
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:54,010
What's that?

473
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:59,460
"I'd rather you be a beggar than do this!"

474
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:06,460
For real?

475
00:35:08,900 --> 00:35:12,210
So much for this. Let's leave this topic behind.

476
00:35:12,970 --> 00:35:14,910
Enjoy your tea.

